New Records: Angola claimed their biggest ever Cup of Nations finals win
Key Match Events: Gelson Dala scored twice, including a goal from a free-kick
Lubeni Haukongo received a red card
Mabululu scored the third goal for Angola
Post-Match Reflections: Angola's coach and players celebrated the win
Angola await a quarter-final tie against the winners of Nigeria vs Cameroon
Miscellaneous Highlights: Angola's goalkeeper Neblu received a red card in the 17th minute
The match was played at the Stade de Bouaké in Bouaké, Ivory Coast with an attendance of 28,663
Others: The Africa Cup of Nations is being held in Ivory Coast
